title.narrative: CAPACITY BUILDING OF HEALTH WORKERS

description.narrative: By 2018, skills of Health Workers in the provision of Maternal, Neonatal, and Child Health (MNCH), HIV/SRH, and nutrition services improved, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2018, 85% of mothers, adolescents, newborns and under-fives, especially the most vulnerable, benefit from access to health care services, including HIV prevention, care, treatment and support.

title.narrative: By 2018, skills of Health Workers in the provision of MNCH, HIV/SRH, and nutrition services improved

description.narrative: In 2018, 1,278 health care workers were trained in different areas and their capacity strengthened on emergency obstetric and newborn care, essential newborn care, Kangaroo Mother Care, focused antenatal care, IYCF and IMNCI. Furthermore, 557 Community Health Workers received refresher trainings on community-based maternal and newborn health. | Status:Met | As-of Date:27/12/2018
